## 4. `.center-bar-holder-container` — Scroll Behavior and Positioning Context

From `home.css`:

**Base (desktop):**
```css
.center-bar-holder-container {
    position: relative;
    align-items: center;
    left: 250px;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    width: 750px;
    height: 100vh;
    /* NO overflow set — scrolling is on .home-parent-container */
}
```
The scroll is on the **parent** `.home-parent-container` which has `overflow-y: auto; overflow-x: hidden`. The center column has `height: 100vh` with no overflow of its own, so it grows to fill and the parent scrolls.

**`@media (max-width: 768px)` — line 325:**
```css
.center-bar-holder-container {
    position: relative;
    align-items: center;
    left: 200px;     /* sidebar narrows from 250px to 200px */
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    width: 550px;
    height: 100vh;
}
```

**`@media (max-width: 428px)` — line 375:**
```css
.center-bar-holder-container {
    position: absolute;     /* switches from relative to absolute */
    left: 1px;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    justify-content: flex-start;
    align-items: center;
    width: 428px;
    height: 100dvh;         /* uses dynamic viewport height */
}
```

**`@media (max-width: 480px)` — line 437:**
```css
.center-bar-holder-container {
    position: absolute;
    left: 1px;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    justify-content: flex-start;
    align-items: center;
    width: 100%;             /* full-width */
    height: 100vh;
}
```

Key positioning observation: on desktop the container is `position: relative` with a static `left: 250px` offset (matching the sidebar width), but on mobile (`<=480px`) it switches to `position: absolute; left: 1px`, which takes it out of normal flow and the sidebar collapses (`display: none`). The `position: fixed` on `.newsfeed-header` means it positions itself relative to the viewport — it is NOT contained by `.center-bar-holder-container` — which is why on desktop `z-index: 120` is needed and on mobile (480px) it jumps to `z-index: 121`.
